  "response": "Starting a business with just $100 is possible with some creativity and strategic planning. Here are some low-cost business ideas:\n\n1. Service-based businesses\n- Freelance writing\n- Social media management\n- Virtual assistant services\n- Pet sitting/dog walking\n- Lawn care/landscaping\n- House cleaning\n- Tutoring\n\n2. Online businesses\n- Dropshipping\n- Print-on-demand merchandise\n- Affiliate marketing\n- Selling digital products (e-books, courses)\n- Content creation/blogging\n- Website design\n\n3. Craft/product-based businesses\n- Handmade crafts on Etsy\n- Jewelry making\n- Candle or soap making\n- Reselling items on eBay/Facebook Marketplace\n- Baking/catering small orders\n\nInitial steps:\n- Create a business plan\n- Register your business (if required)\n- Set up social media accounts\n- Use free marketing tools\n- Invest in minimal supplies\n- Leverage existing skills\n- Start part-time\n- Reinvest initial earnings\n\nTips:\n- Keep overhead costs low\n- Use free online tools\n- Network extensively\n- Provide excellent customer service\n- Gradually reinvest profits\n\nThe key is starting small, being resourceful, and scaling gradually.",
